  abstract = {PGSE and NOE NMR measurements were carried out for complexes [Ru({$\eta$}6-cymene)((2-R-C6H4)NC(Me)C(Me)N(2-R-C6H4))Cl]X (X = BF4 or BPh4) in both protic and aprotic solvents with a relative permettivity ({$\varepsilon$}r) ranging from 2.27 (benzene-d6) to 46.45 (dimethyl sulfoxide-d6). PGSE and NOE results indicate that complexes have a tendency to aggregate even in medium-polarity solvents such as ethanol ({$\varepsilon$}r = 24.55) and methanol ({$\varepsilon$}r = 32.66). In addition, the aggregation process is favored by a decrease of {$\varepsilon$}r and, unexpectedly, by protic solvents. NOE measurement investigations, interpreted with the help of theoretical calculations and confirmed by X-ray single crystal studies, suggest different aggregation processes for the two counteranions:\, two cationic moieties approach each other when X = BF4 while the anion bridges two cationic moieties when X = BPh4.},
